com.ibm.team.process.common.advice

Interface IParticipantReport

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable, IProcessReport
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAdvisorReport

    public interface IParticipantReport
extends IProcessReport
    A report which encapsulates the result of executing an operation participant.

    Severity values have the following meaning for a participant report:

    • IProcessReport.OK - the participant detected no problems
    • IProcessReport.WARNING - the participant detected a problem, but the problem should not prevent the operation from executing
    • IProcessReport.ERROR - the participant detected a problem which should prevent the operation from executing

    Participant reports are automatically created by the process framework when a participant is run.

    Clients may not implement this interface.

    Since:
    0.5
